article.headline: Radford 101, VMI 77
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Chris Oliver and Dan Ross each scored 20 points to lead Radford to a 101-77 win over VMI on Thursday night. The Highlanders (12-7, 5-2 Big South Conference) had its largest lead of 27 points with 5:26 left in the first. Radford was 8-of-16 from 3-point range in the first half, 14-of-29 for the game. The Keydets (7-11, 2-5) trailed 50-31 at the half, shooting 44 percent from the field. Radford was 64.5 percent shooting in the first half. Radford scored 27 points off of the Keydets' 16 turnovers and went 61.7 percent shooting for the game. VMI was held to 45.2 percent. Justin Jarman led the Keydets with a career-high 16 points and eight rebounds, and Fred Robinson added 14. Whit Holcomb-Faye had 17 for Radford, and Andre Bynum added 13. This is the fourth-straight win for Radford.
